HEADWORD: needlecraft
<hw>needlecraft</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An article or
articles created or assembled by needle and thread;
needlework.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> needlework.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The art, process, or occupation of creating objects
with needles, such as in crocheting, embroidery, quilting, or
tapestry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Needlefish</ent>⟦br⟧
